    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-12-05</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-08-21T12:09:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Tax Code Termination Act - Mandates the termination of the Internal Revenue Code after December 31, 2010, except for self-employment taxes, Federal Insurance Contributions Act taxes, and Railroad Retirement taxes. </p> <p>Declares that any new federal tax system should be a simple and fair system that: (1) provides tax relief for working Americans; (2) protects the rights of taxpayers and reduces tax collection abuses; (3) eliminates the bias against savings and investment; (4) promotes economic growth and job creation; and (5) does not penalize marriage or families.</p> <p>Requires that the new federal tax system be approved by Congress in its final form by July 4, 2010.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
